mBox
====

mBox is a JavaScript (MooTools) library, which lets you easily set up tooltips, modal windows, notice messages and more.

Documentation
=============

http://www.htmltweaks.com/mBox/Documentation

Installation
============

To get started, all you need is a new version of MooTools and MooTools More/Element.Measure.
Then include mBox.Core.js together with its CSS file and you are set.

- MooTools 1.4.5
- MooTools More/Element.Measure
- mBox.Core.js
- assets/mBoxCore.css

mBox.Core
=========

A very basic mBox could look like this:

var myMBox = new mBox({
    content: 'This is a very basic mBox. Click anywhere to close.'
});
myMBox.open();

mBox.Tooltip
============

The mBox.Tooltip class extends mBox.Core, helping you to easily attach tooltips to any DOM element.
In following example a tooltip will show up on mouseover of an element with the id="myTooltip1":

new mBox.Tooltip({
    content: 'Default tooltip.',
    attach: 'myTooltip1'
});

mBox.Tooltip
============

With mBox.Modal you can easily install modal dialog windows.
In following example a modal dialog will show up when you click the element with the id="myModalDialog1":

new mBox.Modal({
    title: 'My modal dialog',
    content: 'This is a simple modal dialog window.',
    attach: 'myModalDialog1'
});

mBox.Tooltip
============

With mBox.Notice you can show little notices to your visitors.
Simply create a new instance of mBox.Notice and your notice will pop up immediately:

new mBox.Notice({
    content: 'This is a default notice'
});

Those are only very basic examples, this library can do a lot more. Read the documentation so see what you can do:

http://www.htmltweaks.com/mBox/Documentation